{
  "stem": "2002.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he had a Polish guy working with him in the Communist party.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What looks like that, this Polish guy gave it over to the police as workin' as a spy for the police.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they would arrest him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when they would take him from prison to the police station to question, [? he ?] would pull his hair outta his head and throw it on the street.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "People should see it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they also gave him needles under the nails for him to give out secrets from the Communists.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But when the war broke out, and he escaped to Russia-- and I'm gonna jump now from this time to further-- and when he was in Russia, and then he immigrated to Israel.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when I met him in Israel and I asked him about Communism, he was-- nobody's anti-Communism as he turned anti-Communism, because he was an idealist.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It turned out that Communism is a dictatorship, that Communism does not work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to go back, my other brother, did not-- Moishe, did not belong to any organization.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I belonged to Shomer ha-Tsa'ir.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And one time that was in 1938, I guess, or '37 or '38, we were gonna go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They would pick so many.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every year they would pick so many people to go.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I thought that time was my, but somehow I didn't fall in in that group that time yet.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some of them at that time, my friends there who belonged to that group, went to Israel to be [NON-ENGLISH], because I think it's the-- to be a guard.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A Zionist group.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Who--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, Yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They all-- they all were happy if they know they gonna be goin' there.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
